# Usage

Links are controlled by a small set of state tokens. Start with:

- `--link-color`, `--link-color-visited`, and `--link-color-hover` for state colors
- `--link-decoration` and `--link-decoration-hover` for underline behavior
- `--link-focus-ring-*` tokens to align focus styling with your theme
- `--link-transition-duration` for interaction timing

These tokens inherit semantic color and focus-ring defaults, so overriding them preserves dark-mode variants automatically.

# Tokens

## Link Color Tokens

Control the visual appearance of links in different states. These tokens automatically inherit dark mode behavior from semantic tokens.

| Token                        | Description                              | Default Value                    |
| ---------------------------- | ---------------------------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| `--link-color`               | Default link color                       | `var(--color-accent)`            |
| `--link-color-dark`          | Default link color in dark mode          | `var(--color-accent-dark)`       |
| `--link-color-visited`       | Color for visited links                  | `var(--color-purple-700)`        |
| `--link-color-visited-dark`  | Visited link color in dark mode          | `var(--color-purple-400)`        |
| `--link-color-hover`         | Color when hovering or focused           | `var(--color-blue-700)`          |
| `--link-color-hover-dark`    | Hover/focus color in dark mode           | `var(--color-blue-300)`          |

## Link Decoration Tokens

Control underline visibility and behavior across different link states.

| Token                     | Description                                      | Default Value |
| ------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------ | ------------- |
| `--link-decoration`       | Default text decoration (underline visibility)  | `none`        |
| `--link-decoration-hover` | Text decoration on hover/focus                   | `underline`   |

## Link Interaction Tokens

Control transitions and focus ring styling for enhanced user experience.

| Token                         | Description                                  | Default Value                    |
| ----------------------------- | -------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| `--link-transition-duration`  | Duration of color transitions                | `var(--transition-duration-base)` |
| `--link-focus-ring-width`     | Focus ring outline width                     | `var(--focus-ring-width)`        |
| `--link-focus-ring-color`     | Focus ring outline color                     | `var(--focus-ring-color)`        |
| `--link-focus-ring-offset`    | Focus ring offset from link                  | `var(--focus-ring-offset)`       |
| `--link-focus-border-radius`  | Focus ring border radius                     | `var(--radius-xs)`               |

# Examples

## Default Links

Clean, modern link styling with hover underlines:

```css
:root {
  /* No design token overrides */
}
```

::: style

This is a paragraph with a [default link](https://example.com) that shows underline on hover. Links maintain clean appearance while providing clear interaction feedback.

:::

## Always Underlined Links

Traditional web styling with persistent underlines:

```css
:root {
  --link-decoration: underline;
  --link-decoration-hover: underline;
  --link-color: var(--color-blue-700);
}
```

::: style --link-decoration: underline; --link-decoration-hover: underline; --link-color: var(--color-blue-700);

Traditional [underlined links](https://example.com) maintain the classic web convention where all links are visually distinct through persistent underlines, making them immediately identifiable as clickable elements.

:::

## Subtle Links

Reduced contrast for secondary content areas:

```css
:root {
  --link-color: var(--color-gray-600);
  --link-color-hover: var(--color-gray-900);
  --link-decoration: none;
  --link-decoration-hover: underline;
  --link-transition-duration: var(--transition-duration-slow);
}
```

::: style --link-color: var(--color-gray-600); --link-color-hover: var(--color-gray-900); --link-decoration: none; --link-decoration-hover: underline; --link-transition-duration: var(--transition-duration-slow);

For sidebars, footnotes, or secondary content, [subtle links](https://example.com) use muted colors that don't compete with primary content while still providing clear interaction feedback through slower, more deliberate transitions.

:::

## High Contrast Links

Bold, accessible styling for maximum visibility:

```css
:root {
  --link-color: var(--color-blue-800);
  --link-color-visited: var(--color-purple-800);
  --link-color-hover: var(--color-blue-900);
  --link-decoration: underline;
  --link-decoration-hover: underline;
}
```

::: style --link-color: var(--color-blue-800); --link-color-visited: var(--color-purple-800); --link-color-hover: var(--color-blue-900); --link-decoration: underline; --link-decoration-hover: underline;

For accessibility-focused designs, [high-contrast links](https://example.com) use strong colors and persistent underlines to ensure maximum visibility. [Previously visited links](https://example.com) show distinct purple coloring to help users track their navigation history.

:::


# Tips

**Color accessibility**: Ensure link colors provide sufficient contrast against text and background colors. Test with color contrast analyzers and verify readability in both light and dark modes.

**State differentiation**: Use distinct colors for different link states (default, visited, hover) to help users understand navigation context and interaction feedback.

**Decoration consistency**: Choose decoration patterns that match your content context - clean for modern interfaces, underlined for traditional web content, button-style for calls-to-action.

**Focus visibility**: Never remove focus rings without providing alternative focus indicators. The focus ring tokens ensure keyboard navigation remains accessible while matching your theme's visual style.

**Semantic token leverage**: Link tokens reference semantic colors like `--color-accent` that automatically include dark mode variants. Override `--color-accent` to change the primary link color globally, or override specific `--link-color*` tokens for fine-grained control.

**Transition timing**: Use semantic transition durations for consistency with other interface elements. Slower transitions work well for subtle links, faster transitions for high-interaction contexts.

**Test interaction states**: Verify that hover, focus, and visited states provide clear feedback and maintain accessibility across different devices and input methods.

**Content context**: Consider your content type when choosing link styling - academic papers benefit from subtle styling, marketing content from bold styling, and technical documentation from clear, functional styling.
